Wed. Night 
Dearest Enat:
Grandma went away at noon today. I was out at Blair, Neb., talking to a state school convention when she died, & the wire reached me a half hour later when I was at lunch. At first I planned to leave at once for Branson, but a second wire asked me to meet Aunty Lu <del>and</del> & at K.C. where the body will be cremated: Before I left Branson I made all arrangements with Whelchel for this - at Grandma's request. So it is best for me to meet Aunty Lu at K.C. instead of going ot Branson first, where I could do no good at all, as all was arranged there. 

